At lower values, the nausea effect is replaced with a green overlay.
Controls how much the field of view can change with gameplay effects.

Nearby chunks are compiled in parallel threads. This may result in brief visual holes when blocks are destroyed.
Some actions within a chunk will recompile the chunk immediately. This includes block placing & destroying.
Nearby chunks are always compiled immediately. This may impact game performance when blocks are placed or destroyed.

%s graphics uses screen shaders for drawing weather, clouds, and particles behind translucent blocks and water.
This may severely impact performance for portable devices and 4K displays.

Fancy graphics balances performance and quality for the majority of machines.
Weather, clouds, and particles may not appear behind translucent blocks or water.

Fast graphics reduces the amount of visible rain and snow.
Transparency effects are disabled for various blocks such as leaves.
